\[g^{(i)}=D^{(i)}\cdot P_{\pi_{i}}=\operatorname{diag}\left(d^{(i)}_{1},\ldots, d^{(i)}_{n_{i}}\right)\cdot P_{\pi_{i}}\in\mathcal{G}_{n_{i}}.\] (28)

